 When the listing create the smart-contract will have had the 2xprice amount

documentation.text:
Rate the booking 1-5 stars
 The function checks the msg.sender and validates
 they were either owner or guest in the booking.
 If they were not, a PermissionDenied event is emitted.
 @param bid         the identifier for their booking, this
                    coupled with msg.sender is enough to determine
                    the person being rated
 @param stars       unsigned integer between 1 and 5, anything else
                    will emit an error

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

createListing(uint8,string,uint256).notice: Creates a new listing for the message sender and returns the Id of the created listing When the listing create the smart-contract will have had the 2xprice amount added to its balance.

deleteListing(uint256).notice: Returns the listing balance to its owner and deletes the listing Only if there are no active bookings.

freeJunk().notice: Free all junk storage kept for reuse

fulfilBooking(uint256).notice: Invoked by the guest of a booking after the booking end, confirming the host fulfilled their obligations, and releasing funds held in escrow.

isEmpty().notice: The list is empty if the HEAD node points to itself

rate(uint256,uint256).notice: Rate the booking 1-5 stars The function checks the msg.sender and validates they were either owner or guest in the booking. If they were not, a PermissionDenied event is emitted.

useNextPos().notice: Returns the next available position and updates it
